This project is to create hardware and software to connect a USB-based Garmin GPS to a RS-232 based system. Further, it confgures the GPS to periodically send its coordinates and converts those to NMEA standard sentences before sending it to the RS-232 port.

Useful links:

AT90USB647 Reference:
http://www.atmel.com/dyn/resources/prod_documents/7593S.pdf

AVR USB Library for AT90USBxxx Microcontrollers:
http://www.atmel.com/dyn/resources/prod_documents/doc7675.pdf

Garmin Device Interface Protocol Information:
http://www8.garmin.com/support/commProtocol.html
